Bake in the preheated oven for 35 minutes; remove pie, and cover the rim with aluminum foil to prevent burning. Return to oven, and bake until the middle sets and the top forms a crusty layer, about 15 more minutes. Let the pie cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.', 25.35, 'per portion', 50, 'Textiles', 'East Africa', ARRAY['https://www.themealdb.com/images/media/meals/yrstur1511816601.jpg'], '389g', ARRAY['Organic', 'Top Rated'], '{"calories":630,"protein":48,"carbs":45,"fat":30}'::JSONB, 'This traditional Sugar Pie has been passed down through generations in East Africa.', TRUE, TRUE, NULL, 4.5, 40, NOW(), NOW()),
